  "instructions": [
    "Combine millet and water in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low, cover, and simmer for 20 minutes.",
    "Let the mixture cool, then transfer it to a bowl and mix in salt, olive oil, chopped onion, chopped garlic, and chopped parsley.",
    "Transfer the mixture to a ceramic container and add apple cider vinegar and marjoram. Cover the container with cheesecloth or a clean cotton cloth, securing with a rubber band.",
    "Ferment the mixture at room temperature for 24-48 hours, stirring daily. Once fermented, refrigerate and serve cold.",
    "Serve chilled, garnished with additional parsley if desired."
  ],
